    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for model risk level 3. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is judged acceptable given that the COU is explicitly scoped to static compression-bending per ASTM F1717 and the regulatory decision does not require demonstration across dynamic or multi-axis loading. All three QoI comparisons yield E/uval values below 1.96. The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the declared COU.",
